Subject: Re: [T2] Cranking...cranking...ignition

Sounds like you could have a leaking needle valve to me.  This will make 
your engine run  rich, especially at lower engine speeds.  A piece of 
gunk that was dislodged when the carb was changed, or shuck loose on 
your trip could easily jamb against the needle so that it will not seat 
fully.

Jim

